			Assignment 4: Deliver Program
		</div>

		<div class = "subtitle">PDB files</div>
		<div class = "block">
			<li>The structural information of a protein is saved in a pdb file</li>
			<li><a href = "https://www.rcsb.org/">PDB Repository</a></li>
			<li><a href = "https://www.wwpdb.org/documentation/file-format">PDB Format Documentation</a></li>
			<li>PDB files can be visulized with <a href = "https://www.cgl.ucsf.edu/chimera/">Chimera</a></li>
			<li><a href = "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amino_acid">Amino Acid</a></li>
		</div>
		<div class = "subtitle">Description</div>
		<div class = "block">
			<p style = "text-align:center;"><img src = "img/CS3335_A2.png" width = "60%"></p>
		</div>
		<div class = "block">
			<p style = "text-align:center;"><img src = "img/CS3335_A3.png" width = "40%"></p>
		</div>
		<div class = "block">
			<li>Write a C program to meet the following requirements
				<ol>
					<li>The program read a pdb file name from command line</li>
					<li>The pdb file is parsed into residues</li>
					<li>Generate a center.csv file
						<ul>
							<li>Each residue has a pseudo center, which is the center of N, CA, and C</li>
							<li>Each row in center.csv file contains, residue name, residue index, x, y, z of the center</li>
						</ul>
					</li>
					<li>Generate a cadist.csv file
						<ul>
							<li>Calculate the distance between CA atom in reisdue i and CA atom in residue i+1</li>
						</ul>
					</li>
				</ol>
			</li>
		</div>
		<div class = "block">
		<pre class = "prettyprint linenums">
// Atom.h
#ifndef ATOM_H
#define ATOM_H

typedef struct
{
	char atomName[10];
	char residueName[10];
	char chain[10];
	int atomIndex;
	int residueIndex;
	float x, y, z;
} Atom;

#endif
		</pre>
		</div>
		<div class = "block">
		<pre class = "prettyprint linenums">
// Residue.h
#ifndef RESIDUE_H
#define RESIDUE_H

#include "Atom.h"

typedef struct
{
	int atomNum;
	Atom *atoms;
} Residue;

#endif
		</pre>
		</div>
